<br>
(as much as I hate replying to my myself, I have to vent a bit. I'm a &quot;little&quot; annoyed just about now)<br>
<br>
Before 14.0, people would find missions, and have them ready so that when they would find a team, they could just jump into the mission and start hunting.<br>
<br>
What has happened now is that all people are LFG'ing by the most popular mission terminals, because you now have to have the WHOLE team by the terminal when you get the mission.<br>
<br>
As the patch notes say: <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Only team members who are present when the mission is created will receive a team mission icon, and a reward. If you join the team later, you can get into the mission area using the key duplicator, as with solo missions - but you will get no reward.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
That means that in locations like newland, where many mid to high levels prefer to find missions, there are now so many people that it's impossible to move around, or even zone in or out of the area. <br>
<br>
And if you somehow find a team somewhere else, and then head on over to the mission terminals to find a mission, chances are that atleast half your teammembers will go LD while trying to zone in to (for example) Newland City, because it's so horribly overcrowded. <br>
